      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17/8/87 ¶  ¶ When in the latter part of the year, dear Mr Dyer, I shall have finished the “Key to the syst. of Vict. plants”, ¶ B88.11.02. ¶  ¶ I will first of all elaborate Mr Forbes dicotyledonous p...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.08.17c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Thiselton-Dyer</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, f. 227.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Date stamped twice</seg>: Royal Gardens Kew 3 Oct 1887.</p>
               </note>17/8/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When in the latter part of the year, dear Mr Dyer, I shall have finished the “Key to the syst. of Vict. plants”,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.11.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will first of all elaborate Mr Forbes dicotyledonous plants from New Guinea,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>M had agreed with the British Museum (Natural History) on responsibilities for describing the plants collected in New Guinea by Henry Forbes in 1885 and 1886, meaning that he would describe the dicotyledonous species;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see W. Carruthers to M, 1 March 1886.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a not quite complete set of which came to me in return for the subsidy, given to Mr F. (£500 - - ) by the Royal Geogr. Soc of Australia on my proposition as President of the Vict. branch. I shall then most willingly divide any specimen, admitting of division, and thus share the set with Kew.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall then ...<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Kew<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">is marked with a red pencil line in the margin and annotated above that</seg>: Prof 0. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>/<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Oliver has added</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Good D.0.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should like very much, that in autumn, when this letter will arrive, your Establishment would send me in a small close box as ordinary merchandise nailed down, a plant of Vaccinium Myrtillus,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vaccinium Myrtillus<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">is underlined in red pencil</seg>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which then will be in a dormant state.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Annotation in red ink next to ‘in a small ... Myrtillus’</seg>: Seeds sent 29-10-87.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">See M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">D.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Morris, 10 December 1887.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I am satisfied, if a common wooden box without metal-lining is chosen, and the plant is dried of superficial moisture and without earth is partially placed horizontally into some<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">almost</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">dry</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sphagnum, it will arrive quite alive, and I could then take it at once to our sub-alpine country.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This experiment, even should it fail would cost little and could be recorded in your Bulletin<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Paragraph written in left margin, f.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>227 front.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>How easy will it be to those coming after us, when they can use tens of thousands of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>illustrat[.]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Paragraph written in central margin f.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>227 back.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Vaccinium Myrtillus</p>
         </div>
      </body>
